description:
On an alphabet board, we start at position (0, 0), corresponding to character board[0][0].

Here, board = [ "abcde ", "fghij ", "klmno ", "pqrst ", "uvwxy ", "z "], as shown in the diagram below.

We may make the following moves:

*   'U' moves our position up one row, if the position exists on the board;
*   'D' moves our position down one row, if the position exists on the board;
*   'L' moves our position left one column, if the position exists on the board;
*   'R' moves our position right one column, if the position exists on the board;
*   '!' adds the character board[r][c] at our current position (r, c) to the answer.

(Here, the only positions that exist on the board are positions with letters on them.)

Return a sequence of moves that makes our answer equal to target in the minimum number of moves. You may return any path that does so.

solutionCode.javascript:
    ```javascript
function maxSatisfied(customers, grumpy, minutes) {
    let total = 0, maxIncrease = 0, windowIncrease = 0;
    for (let i = 0, j = 0; i < customers.length; ++i) {
        if (i - j === minutes) {
            windowIncrease -= customers[j] * grumpy[j];
            ++j;
        }
        windowIncrease += customers[i] * grumpy[i];
        total += customers[i] * (1 - grumpy[i]);
        maxIncrease = Math.max(maxIncrease, windowIncrease);
    }
    return total + maxIncrease;
}
```

    1. Initialize total customers satisfied, max increase, and the window increase as all 0s.
2. Use two pointers i, and j. Iterate through every customer in the array.
3. If the difference between i and j is equal to the given minutes, then reduce the window increase by customers[j] multiplied by grumpy[j] and increment j.
4. Add customers[i] multiplied by grumpy[i] to the window increase.
5. Add customers[i] multiplied by (1 - grumpy[i]) to the total satisfied customers.
6. Calculate the maximum increase by comparing the current max increase with the window increase.
7. At the end, return the total + maxIncrease as the maximum number of satisfied customers.

